{
  "stem": "9701.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so I continued to still hope to be reunited with my parents somewhere.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in 1983, I learned that my mother indeed was sent to Auschwitz on September 11th, 1942.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My father was already sent there on August 19th, 1942.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And all my other family members who were in Gurs or some of the other camps in France, they all between August and September 1942 were sent to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "None of them have ever been heard from again.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The only one that I was able to find out-- find out some information about is my father's youngest brother, Oskar.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I understand he arrived in Auschwitz on August 12th 1942 and died there on I believe it was August 27th 1942, of some intestinal problems allegedly.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I only got that information a couple years ago.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The Russians released some information about Auschwitz, and I requested information about my parents and everyone else.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And that's the only information I was able to obtain.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] In 1980, I went back to Europe to visit most of the camps that my parents had been to.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I went to Gurs, to Dachau, and the last place was Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And when I stood on the ramp in Auschwitz where when the trains arrived and people got off the trains and the selection was made as to who will live a few-- maybe live a few more days or weeks and be put to work because they were young enough and strong enough and the rest were sent to the gas chambers because they were too old, had young children, or were too sick, when I stood on that ramp in September 1980 I finally accepted the fact that my parents indeed did not survive.",
      "word_count": 95
    }
  ],
